import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QuickSummary from '../components/QuickSummary.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Squad Building" 
  description="Main Squad First philosophy, UR hero focus, Tank squad strategy for mid-game, Monica for Doomed Elites, and practical mono-type builds for Last War: Survival."
>
  <h1>Squad Building</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-[#8a96b0]">This is the most important section on the site. Read it twice.</p>

  <QuickSummary title="The Core Rule">
    <p><strong>Main Squad First.</strong> Concentrate the vast majority of your shards, skill medals, gear, and research into one squad. A dominant #1 squad lets you clear content that would otherwise require three average squads. Your second and third squads can be 60–70% as strong and still be effective.</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>Squad Basics</h2>
  <ul class="space-y-2">
    <li>Each squad is <strong>5 heroes</strong> in a fixed formation.</li>
    <li><strong>Mono-type squads only</strong> (all Tank, all Aircraft, or all Missile). The type bonus is too strong to ignore (~20% effective power in most matchups).</li>
    <li>Positioning matters: Frontline draws fire, backline focuses damage. Use the in-game formation view.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The Tank Squad Exception (Mid-Game Reality)</h2>
  <p>Many experienced mid-game players run <strong>two full Tank squads</strong> before heavily investing in Aircraft or Missile. Tank is durable, forgiving for F2P/low spenders, and excellent for PvE, gathering, and defense.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0] mt-2">Only start a serious second type once your primary Tank squad has most core heroes at 4–5 stars with decent gear and skills.</p>

  <h2>UR Hero Focus</h2>
  <p>UR heroes are the long-term endgame. Their base stats and skill ceilings are significantly higher. However, well-built SSR heroes (especially season promotables like Mason, Scarlett, etc.) can carry you through most mid-game content.</p>
  <p><strong>Transition rule:</strong> Keep 1–2 strong SSR/promotable heroes in your main squad while you slowly replace them with UR as you pull and star them up. Do not bench a 5-star SSR for a 1-star UR.</p>

  <h2>Monica — The Elite Farmer</h2>
  <div class="quick-summary">
    <p><strong>Slot Monica</strong> into your Doomed Elite rallies (lead or just participate). Her "Treasure Hunter" skill gives a large resource bonus (Metal, Food, Gold, and other RSS) on elites and regular zombies — reports range from +30% at low investment to +70%+ when skilled up.</p>
    <p class="mt-2">Investment level: 3–4 stars + skill level ~10 is usually enough. Do not max her over your main combat heroes.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Practical Mid-Game Builds (Examples)</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-[#8a96b0]">These are directionally correct for many servers. Adjust based on what you actually have starred. Always prioritize your highest-starred heroes in the right positions.</p>

  <h3 class="text-base mt-6">Example Tank Squad (Mid-Game Focus)</h3>
  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Position</th><th>Hero</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Front Left (Main Tank)</td><td>Williams / Murphy</td><td>Draws fire, high durability</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Front Right</td><td>Murphy / Lucius</td><td>Secondary support</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Back Left (Primary DPS)</td><td>Kimberly (Kim)</td><td>Highest priority UR / promotable</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Back Center</td><td>Stetmann</td><td>Strong all-rounder</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Back Right</td><td>Marshall / Adam</td><td>Support / secondary DPS</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p class="text-xs text-[#5e6b85]">Other strong Tank options: Scarlett (promotable), Mason (promotable), Carlie (sometimes flex).</p>

  <h3 class="text-base mt-6">When to Start Aircraft or Missile</h3>
  <p>Once your main Tank squad is reliably clearing the content you care about (most Alliance events, decent Arena ranking, strong Doomed Elite performance). Then begin a second squad of the type that counters your server's meta.</p>

  <div class="mt-8 p-4 border border-[#3a4966] rounded text-sm">
    <strong>Pro tip:</strong> Take screenshots of your formation and gear priorities. The difference between a "good" and "great" squad is often 10–15% better positioning and focused upgrades on 2–3 key pieces.
  </div>
</Layout>